message.raw:
feature: added new interface for delaying decoding of base64 binary arrays

* Added a new mixin class in auxiliay, BinaryDataArrayTransformer
  which encapsulates the process of converting a base64 bytestring
  into a numpy array.
  - If decoding is done immediately, the functionality is essentially
    identical to previous implementation.
  - If decoding is off (decode_binary=False), instead of discarding the
    base64 bytestring and the associated compression information, it
    creates a namedtuple which records the bytestring, the compression
    type and the dtype of the encoded array, with a method to decode the
    array later.
  - Adapted the decompression process to permit more than just zlib compression,
    supporting the addition of future decompressor implementations.
* Modified xml.ArrayConversionMixin to inherit from aux.BinaryDataArrayTransformer
  which splices the class into the inheritance hierarchy for mzml.MzML and
  mzxml.MzXML.
* Modified mzml.MzML to use the new BinaryDataArrayTransformer API instead of
  the single call aux._decode_base64_data_array.
  - Altered MzML._determine_compression to recover the compression
    type as a string instead of as a boolean without information about which
    compression method was used.
  - Altered MzML._handle_binary to use decode_data_array when decoding arrays
    and _make_record when not.
* Modified mzxml.MzXML to use the new API as in mzml.MzML.

message.raw:
Added a check in ByteCountingXMLScanner to account for cases where the assumption
that all files start with the first byte belonging to the doctype declaration. This
assumption was violated by the presence of a BOM, which was unintentionally padded
with a delimiting character, causing all byte offsets counted to be off by 1 byte.

message.raw:
Replaced __repr__ method of unit-values with default behavior, and instead
fall back on _repr_pretty_ in IPython displaying unit information. This is
to avoid breaking common libraries that assume that assume that __repr__ of
primitives will always just produce the primitive value.

Also fixed a problem with mzXML iteration that prevented it from working on
correctly ordered but un-nested scans.
